Package: pilot-link
Version: 0.10.99
Revision: 5
GCC: 3.1
Depends: readline (>= 4.3-5), %N-bin (= %v-%r), %N-shlibs (= %v-%r)
BuildDepends: fink (>= 0.9.9)
BuildDependsOnly: true
Replaces: %N (<< %v-5)
Source: http://pilot-link.org/source/%n-%v.tar.gz
Patch: %f.patch
ConfigureParams: --with-pic --enable-shared --enable-static --without-tcl --without-itcl --without-tk --without-java --without-python --mandir=%i/share/man --infodir=%p/share/info --libexecdir=%p/lib
InstallScript: <<
  mkdir -p %i/lib
  cp libpisock++/.libs/*.dylib %i/lib
  make install prefix=%i
<<
SetCFLAGS: -no-cpp-precomp
Splitoff: <<
  Package: %N-shlibs
  Replaces: %N (<< %v-5)
  Suggests: %N-bin
  Files: <<
    lib/libpisock.*.dylib 
    lib/libpisock++.*.dylib
  <<
  DocFiles: COPYING* ChangeLog README
<<
Splitoff2: <<
  Package: %N-bin
  Depends: %N-shlibs (= %v-%r)
  Replaces: %N (<< %v-5)
  Files: <<
    bin
    share/man
    share/pilot-link
  <<
  DocFiles: COPYING* ChangeLog README
<<
DocFiles: COPYING* README
Description: Palm libraries                             
DescDetail: <<
Pilot-Link is the tools and toys needed to connect your Palm or Palm
compatible handheld (including Handspring, Sony, and Palm) with Unix
and Linux machines.
<<
DescPort: <<
Had to disable tcl/tk support till the maintainer of either x11 or tcltk
fixes a header file.
<<
License: GPL
Maintainer: Justin F. Hallett <thesin@users.sourceforge.net>
Homepage: http://www.pilot-link.org/
